ransfer rate. Though the proportion of Ap/Bp stars in\nintermediate-mass stars is only 5\\%, the lifetime of the UCXB phase is\n$\\gtrsim$ 2 Gyr, producing a relatively high number of observable systems,\nmaking this an alternative evolutionary channel for the formation of UCXBs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 6 Aug 2016 10:04:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-24"}
